First, I wonder if `py3status --interval` is a dead config.
Second, I wonder if it would be better if `py3status` could reload config when users do `killall -SIGUSR1 py3status`. Otherwise, we have to `i3 restart` to get new changes.

With this in place, then users could do much more than changing `cache_timeout`. Users could also enable/disable/change modules. Change colors, formats, and more.

Maybe if we move `--interval` to config instead...
```python
py3status {
    # rename interval to cache_timeout

    # replace cache_timeout in all modules if set
    # (and is less than the given cache_timeout)
    cache_timeout = 30

    # replace cache_timeout in all modules if set and on_battery
    # (and is less than the given cache_timeout_on_battery)
    cache_timeout_on_battery = 60
}
```

