@ohemorange : your suggestion of having different certificates doesn't solve the problem. You still have to stop nginx to run the standalone server to renew mail.XXXXX.com, and so you may as well renew the single certificate that way.

The problem is that this is a live server, and that doing it this way causes a potentially unacceptable outage of the web service.

What would be a lot better is if the standalone method didn't have to use port 443, and could use a port not used by any of the standard services.

